text:
Gunnar Uldall (17 November 1940 – 14 November 2017) was a German politician. He was state minister of Economy and Labour in Hamburg from 2001 to 2008. He was born in Hamburg. He was a member of the Christian Democratic Union (CDU). He served on the Hamburg Parliament from 1966 through 1983.
Uldall died on 14 November 2017, shortly before his 77th birthday in Hamburg.
